body:
@fjy @binlijin @b-slim all comments addressed.

@cheddar regarding the Math.min(..) comment, why not simply do following.
`
Math.min(query.getContextValue(CTX_KEY_MAX_RESULTS, config.getMaxResults()), config.getMaxResults);
`

but with this, user can only reduce the limits at query time but never increase. our use case is that of reducing but others might have cases where they want to up the limits. ( @binlijin  what kind of use case do you have ? )

@b-slim Other firehoses have throttles that prevent the log messages from being flooded by repeat messages.

I don't know enough about the firehose in question to know how likely multiple CRC errors in a row are.

If MULTIPLE crc errors in a row are possible, then we'll need throttling on the log (only X messages per second or similar)
